<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1289,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1289,1316]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Tegmina widened, apex rounded, posterior margin curved, forming an angle of 130° in cubital region (
<figureCitation box="[159,237,1325,1351]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,913,938]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,206,884]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,198,887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Acropsis tectiformis, left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833507/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[291,307,1325,1352]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1759,1784]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,452,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,452,1733]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Acropsis tectiformis, male specimen alive. A–B: habitus, lateral view; C: head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833515" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833515/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">6</figureCitation>
), giving a unique aspect to this katydid among 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[836,990,1325,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Microcentrini">Microcentrini</taxonomicName>
genera. Mesosternum and metasternum laterally compressed (
<figureCitation box="[397,493,1361,1387]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[506,537,1362,1388]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1363,194,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Acropsis solimoesensis sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">7E</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[591,641,1361,1387]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[259,1330,281,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[248,1338,273,1877]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Acropsis julianae sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833523/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">10E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1289,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
Redescription. Head apex rounded in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[777,865,1397,1423]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Fastigium and vertex not fused. Compound eyes globular (
<figureCitation box="[262,338,1433,1459]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
B–C). Pronotal carina rounded (
<figureCitation box="[710,785,1433,1459]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
C–D). Lateral lobes of pronotum subrectangular anterior margin straight, ventrally curved and posteriorly sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[807,897,1469,1495]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Furcal sutures connected (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1303,1469,1495]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum and metasternum laterally compressed (
<figureCitation box="[665,753,1505,1531]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum diamond-shaped, with lateral lobes triangular, narrow, Mesosternum and metasternum laterally compressed (
<figureCitation box="[899,996,1541,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1010,1041,1542,1568]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1363,194,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1373,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Acropsis solimoesensis sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">7E</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1098,1147,1541,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[259,1330,281,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[248,1338,273,1877]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Acropsis julianae sp. nov., holotype male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view.Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833523/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">10E</figureCitation>
). Tegmina widened, apex rounded, posterior margin curved, forming an angle of 130° in cubital region (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1135,1577,1603]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,913,938]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,206,884]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,198,887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Acropsis tectiformis, left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833507/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1195,1211,1577,1604]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1759,1784]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,452,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,452,1733]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Acropsis tectiformis, male specimen alive. A–B: habitus, lateral view; C: head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833515" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833515/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">6</figureCitation>
). Vein R somewhat straight and parallel sided with vein MA, distally with several delicate sinuous ramifications (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1269,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,913,938]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,206,884]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,198,887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Acropsis tectiformis, left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833507/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). A pentagonal or hexagonal cell present between veins MP and CuA (
<figureCitation box="[763,832,1649,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,913,938]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,206,884]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,198,887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Acropsis tectiformis, left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833507/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Veins MA and MP bifid distally (
<figureCitation box="[1221,1290,1649,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,913,938]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,206,884]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,198,887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Acropsis tectiformis, left tegmina of male in dorsal view. Abbreviations: AP: Posterior anal vein; AA: anterior anal vein; CuA: anterior cubital vein; CuP: posterior cubital vein; MA: anterior median vein; MP: posterior median vein; R: radial vein; Sc: subcostal vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833507/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Left stridulatory file convex, with median region elevated (
<figureCitation box="[696,786,1685,1711]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2019,2044]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1032,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1032,1994]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acropsis tectiformis, stridulatory file of male. A: left file; B: right file." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833509/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Basal teeth short, gradually increasing in length towards median region (
<figureCitation box="[331,423,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2019,2044]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1032,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1032,1994]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acropsis tectiformis, stridulatory file of male. A: left file; B: right file." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833509/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Median teeth slender, close to each other (
<figureCitation box="[930,1021,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,2019,2044]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1032,1994]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1032,1994]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acropsis tectiformis, stridulatory file of male. A: left file; B: right file." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833509/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Fore femur straight without spines (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Fore tibia with tympanic opening fully opened and three ventral spines (
<figureCitation box="[1077,1161,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Mid femur rectangular without spines (
<figureCitation box="[332,423,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia narrow, slender, without projections (
<figureCitation box="[993,1084,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). All legs with numerous short bristles (
<figureCitation box="[247,318,1829,1855]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[227,1359,188,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[217,1370,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Acropsis tectiformis, male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: head, frontal view; C: head and pronotum, dorsal view; D: head and pronotum, lateral view; E: Thoracic sternites, ventral view; F: foreleg, lateral view; G: midleg, lateral view; H: hindleg, lateral view; I–J: Terminalia in ventral and dorsal view respectively; K: Apex of cerci, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Mes: mesobasisternum; Met: metabasisternum; Cer: cerci; Sty: styli; Pl: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833505/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
F–H). Internal male genitalia with dorsal lobes curved, posteriorly narrowed and overlapping part of upper folds of ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[464,533,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[189,1423,181,1308]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[164,1423,181,1308]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Acropsis tectiformis, male internal genitalia.A–B: phallus, ventral view; C–D: phallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: DF: dorsal fold; DL: dorsal lobe(s); EV: ejaculatory vesicles; TI: titillator process; Lw. vl.: lower folds of ventral lobe; Up. vl.: upper folds of ventral lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3833511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3833511/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
